titleInfo.title: (HC) Wells v. Swarthout
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER signed by Magistrate Judge Craig M. Kellison on 1/03/13 ordering petitioner shall submit on the form provided by the clerk of the court within 30 days from the date of this order, a complete application for leave to proceed in forma pauperis or pay the appropriate filing fee. The clerk of the court is directed to send petitioner a new form application for leave to proceed in forma pauperis. Within 30 days of the date of this order petitioner shall show cause in writing why this action should not be dismissed for lack of jurisdiction. (Plummer, M)

titleInfo.title: (HC) Wells v. Swarthout
titleInfo.subTitle: [DISREGARD - ENTERED DUE TO CLERICAL ERROR]ORDER signed by Magistrate Judge Craig M. Kellison on 1/30/13 granting 5 Motion to Proceed IFP. Plaintiff is obligated to pay the statutory filing fee of $350.00 for this action. All fees shall be collected in accordanc with this order to the CDC. Also, DIRECTING MONTHLY PAYMENTS be made from Prison Account of Andre Wells. CDC is to collect payments from plaintiff's account and forward to the clerk until the $350.00 filing fee is paid in full. Clerk to serve this order and a copy of plaintiff's IFP on the Director of CDC. Clerk to also serve Financial with a copy of this order. (cc: CDC Director and Financial). (Plummer, M) Modified on 1/30/2013 (Plummer, M).
